    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Sara Mosle's heartfelt article does nothing more than hem readers into the same choice we've heard about for years: either individuals or the government must do more. Neither is necessarily true. What poor children clearly need are families who can adequately care for them -- which means the ultimate responsibility lies with parents who ought not to bring children into the world without the proper means to raise them.</p>
        <p>Mitch Horowitz  New York</p>
